---
title: Spicy Green Coconut Curry with Shrimp plus Cilantro-Lime Rice
description: If that craving for a rich, flavorful curry can’t wait, you’re in luck! Shrimp, green beans, and onion simmer in a spicy green coconut curry infused with chilis, lemongrass, and garlic. Spoon it all over fluffy jasmine rice, then finish with a sprinkle of cilantro and a squeeze of fresh lime juice.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/685a7fb2559308f509950b43-572355a0.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/685a7fb2559308f509950b43-en-US.pdf
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-green-coconut-curry-with-shrimp-685a7fb2559308f509950b43
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Southeast Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 95 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2050 mg
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@onion{1}(thinly sliced). Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; halve crosswise
(leave any smaller green beans whole). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop
@cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
onion and green beans; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While veggies cook, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with
#paper towels{}.

Add another large drizzle of cooking oil to pan with veggies. Add shrimp; lightly
season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are lightly browned,
~{1-2%minutes} (they'll finish cooking in the next step).

Reduce heat to medium low and add @green curry paste{2%tablespoon}. Cook,
stirring constantly, until mixture is fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1} in container before opening.

To pan with shrimp, add coconut milk, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @seafood stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/4%cup},
@sugar{1%tsp}, and juice from half the lime (1/2 cup water and 2 tsp sugar for 4
servings). Stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until sauce has thickened and shrimp are cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Taste and season with salt; add another squeeze of lime juice if
desired.

> For an extra-rich curry, stir in 1 TBSP butter; 2 TBSP for 4 servings.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest and half the cilantro. Season with salt
and pepper.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with coconut shrimp curry and remaining
cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.